    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5 min<span class=\"text-danger\"> [10 min]</span> to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-cheesy-portobello-mushroom-risotto/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-cheesy-portobello-mushroom-risotto/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>portobello mushrooms</strong> to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Sprinkle<strong> half </strong>of the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) into the mushrooms \u2013 these are your <strong>cheesy portobellos</strong></p><p>Set the tray aside until later</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-cheesy-portobello-mushroom-risotto/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash the <strong>rocket</strong>, then pat it dry with <strong>kitchen paper</strong></p><p>Wash the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> thoroughly to remove any grit from between the leaves, then top, tail and slice into rounds</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> leek rounds</strong> to the casserole dish</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-cheesy-portobello-mushroom-risotto/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>arborio rice</strong> to the dish and stir everything together</p><p>Crush the <strong>garlic cloves</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife</p><p>Remove the skins<strong> </strong>and chop the<strong> crushed garlic </strong>roughly</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-cheesy-portobello-mushroom-risotto/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Tear the<strong> chestnut mushrooms</strong> directly into the dish</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> with the <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and <strong>white wine vinegar</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>with 600ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.2L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-cheesy-portobello-mushroom-risotto/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, then cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven</p><p>Put the<strong> </strong>tray with the<strong> cheesy portobellos </strong>on into the oven at the same time</p><p>Cook everything for 25-30 min or until the rice is cooked with a slight bite and the portobellos are tender and juicy</p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-cheesy-portobello-mushroom-risotto/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Stir the<strong> remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong> through the risotto and season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Top the risotto with the <strong>cheesy portobellos </strong>and a grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> oven-baked cheesy portobello mushroom risotto</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>oven-baked cheesy portobello mushroom risotto </strong>with the<strong> rocket</strong> to the side</p><p>Let everyone dig in!</p>",
